# README Maintenance Rule

## Overview
The README must always be kept up to date when architectural or usage changes are made to the Clustera YouTube Ingest project.

## Key Documentation Files
- [SPECIFICATION.md](mdc:SPECIFICATION.md) - Technical specification and architecture
- [ABSTRACT.md](mdc:ABSTRACT.md) - Project overview and summary
- [.env.example](mdc:.env.example) - Configuration template

## When to Update README
The README should be updated whenever changes are made to:

### Architecture Changes
- Database schema modifications (Section 3 in [SPECIFICATION.md](mdc:SPECIFICATION.md))
- Pipeline stages or workflow changes (Section 4 in [SPECIFICATION.md](mdc:SPECIFICATION.md))
- SDK design or core classes (Section 5 in [SPECIFICATION.md](mdc:SPECIFICATION.md))
- Technology stack updates (Section 2.2 in [SPECIFICATION.md](mdc:SPECIFICATION.md))

### Usage Changes
- CLI commands or interface modifications (Section 6 in [SPECIFICATION.md](mdc:SPECIFICATION.md))
- Configuration requirements or environment variables (Section 7 in [SPECIFICATION.md](mdc:SPECIFICATION.md))
- Installation or setup procedures
- API interfaces or SDK methods (Section 5.2 in [SPECIFICATION.md](mdc:SPECIFICATION.md))

### Project Structure Changes
- New directories or major file reorganization
- Dependency changes or requirements updates
- Build or deployment process modifications

## README Content Requirements
The README should include:
1. **Project Description** - Aligned with [ABSTRACT.md](mdc:ABSTRACT.md)
2. **Installation Instructions** - Including environment setup from [.env.example](mdc:.env.example)
3. **Usage Examples** - Reflecting current CLI commands from [SPECIFICATION.md](mdc:SPECIFICATION.md)
4. **Architecture Overview** - High-level summary of components from [SPECIFICATION.md](mdc:SPECIFICATION.md)
5. **Configuration Guide** - Based on Section 7 of [SPECIFICATION.md](mdc:SPECIFICATION.md)
6. **Development Setup** - Including database initialization (Section 4.0)
7. **Contributing Guidelines** - If applicable

## Enforcement
- Always review README when modifying [SPECIFICATION.md](mdc:SPECIFICATION.md)
- Update README before committing architectural changes
- Ensure CLI examples in README match actual implementation
- Verify configuration examples are current with [.env.example](mdc:.env.example)
- Cross-reference with [ABSTRACT.md](mdc:ABSTRACT.md) for consistency
